  "local_port": 52326,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What social media platforms are best to use for a restaurant and how often should someone post?",
  "response": "For a restaurant, leveraging social media platforms effectively can significantly boost visibility, engagement, and customer loyalty. Here are the best platforms to use, tailored to a restaurant\u2019s needs, and how often to post:\n\n---\n\n### **Best Platforms for Restaurants**\n1. **Instagram**  \n   - *Why?* Instagram is highly visual, perfect for showcasing food, drinks, ambiance, and events. Features like Stories, Reels, and Guides are great for engaging audiences.  \n   - *What to Post:* High-quality food photos, behind-the-scenes content, special offers, and user-generated content.  \n   - *Posting Frequency:*  \n     - Feed: 3\u20135 times per week.  \n     - Stories: Daily (3\u20135 updates).  \n     - Reels: 1\u20132 times per week.  \n\n2. **Facebook**  \n   - *Why?* Facebook is ideal for building a community, sharing events, and targeting local audiences with ads.  \n   - *What to Post:* Menu updates, specials, events, customer testimonials, and live videos.  \n   - *Posting Frequency:* 3\u20135 times per week.  \n\n3. **TikTok**  \n   - *Why?* TikTok is great for viral content and reaching a younger audience. Short, engaging videos can showcase your restaurant\u2019s personality.  \n   - *What to Post:* Cooking demos, food trends, challenges, and fun behind-the-scenes videos.  \n   - *Posting Frequency:* 1\u20133 times per week.  \n\n4. **Twitter (X)**  \n   - *Why?* Twitter is useful for quick updates, engaging with customers, and responding to feedback.  \n   - *What to Post:* Daily specials, promotions, replies to customers, and industry-related content.  \n   - *Posting Frequency:* 1\u20133 times daily.  \n\n5. **YouTube**  \n   - *Why?* YouTube is ideal for longer-form content like cooking tutorials, chef interviews, or virtual tours of your restaurant.  \n   - *What to Post:* Recipes, event highlights, and storytelling videos.  \n   - *Posting Frequency:* 1\u20132 times per month.  \n\n6. **Pinterest**  \n   - *Why?* Pinterest is great for sharing visually appealing content like recipes, food photography, and event ideas.  \n   - *What to Post:* Infographics, recipe pins, and styled food shots.  \n   - *Posting Frequency:* 5\u201310 pins per week.  \n\n7. **Google My Business (GMB)**  \n   - *Why?* GMB ensures your restaurant appears in local searches and Google Maps. It\u2019s essential for attracting local customers.  \n   - *What to Post:* Updates on hours, specials, events, and photos of your restaurant.  \n   - *Posting Frequency:* 1\u20132 times per week.  \n\n---\n\n### **General Tips for Posting**\n- **Quality Over Quantity:** Focus on high-quality, engaging content rather than posting too frequently.  \n- **Consistency:** Stick to a consistent posting schedule to keep your audience engaged.  \n- **Engage with Followers:** Respond to comments, messages, and reviews promptly.  \n- **Use Hashtags:** On platforms like Instagram and Twitter, use relevant and location-based hashtags to reach a wider audience.  \n- **Analyze Performance:** Use platform insights to track what works and adjust your strategy accordingly.  \n\n---\n\n### **Key Platforms to Prioritize**\nFor most restaurants, **Instagram** and **Facebook** should be the primary focus, with **TikTok** and **Google My Business** as secondary priorities. Adjust based on your target audience and goals.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
